ads.author: Michael Mapes
ads.title: Kraken Plus Virtual Pinball Machine - Ultimate Gaming for Your Home!
ads.description:
Enhance your home entertainment with the Kraken Plus Virtual Pinball Machine from The Pinball King! This cutting-edge machine combines the charm of traditional pinball with modern technology for an unbeatable gaming experience. Price is firm! This is a brand new item custom made by me and my two person crew.

Key Features:
- 43" 4K Playfield Monitor: Enjoy stunning, lifelike visuals that bring each pinball game to life.
- 32" 1080p Backglass Monitor: Adds to the immersion with detailed, high-definition artwork and displays.
- 15.6" HD DMD Monitor: Keeps you informed with bright and clear scoring and game information.
- Realistic Force Feedback System: Feel every nudge, bump, and tilt with precision feedback.
- Accurate Digital Plunger: Mimics the feel of a classic pinball machine for a genuine experience.
- Customizable RGB LED Lighting: Set the mood with dynamic lighting effects that can be tailored to your preferences.
- High-Fidelity Sound System: Immerse yourself in rich, clear sound effects and music.

Why Choose Kraken Plus?
- Perfect for All Ages: Ideal for family fun, parties, or just a relaxing game night.
- Local Business: We are based in Pinellas Park, Florida. Visit us to try out the machine and see its quality firsthand.

Step up your game room with the Kraken Plus Virtual Pinball Machine. It's perfect for both casual players and serious enthusiasts!

Price: 6500
Location: Pinellas Park, Florida

Contact us today to find out more or to schedule a demo!

ads.title: Pac land arcade machine
ads.description:
Needs some ajusting to the picture but other than that it works grate!
Excellent condition !!!

A cute game where Pac-Man, having arms, legs and a face, travels through scrolling cartoon worlds avoiding obstacles in a quest to help a lost fairy get home. Ghosts chase him on pogo sticks and in cars, aeroplanes and flying saucers. Hidden bonuses include fruit, flying boots, etc.

Pac-Land was produced by Bally Midway in 1984.

Bally Midway released 96 machines in our database under this trade name, starting in 1980. Bally Midway was based in United States.

Other machines made by Bally Midway during the time period Pac-Land was produced include: E2088, Gold Ball, Grand Slam (4 player version), Domino Man, Discs Of Tron, Granny and the Gators, Black Pyramid, Ten Pin Champ, Spy Hunter, and Kings of Steel

The cabinet was rebuilt and repainted in 2017, with new vinyl and t-molding installed. The marquee bracket, coin doors and coin bucket holder were also repainted. The only vinyl that is still original is the control panel, but plexiglass cover was replaced. The coin mechanisms are complete and functional, with matching locks for both coin doors, as well as the back cabinet door. It has a 19" Sharp Image CRT monitor with a beautiful and sharp (no pun intended) picture. It currently has 2" locking casters installed for ease of movement.

It currently has a Metal Slug cartridge installed, as the 161 in 1 multi-cart started to flake out. It is included with the sale. It plays well and has been stable, having been taken to Momo Con, Furry Weekend Atlanta and Southern-Fried Gaming Expo a few times over the years.

Given the age of this game, it is sold not DOA (Dead on Arrival), but otherwise as-is. It is local pickup only from Tucker, Georgia. Sale is starting at $900, with payment by cash or PayPal.

More pictures of the game and the rebuild are available here:
https://playeronearcadeservices.com/for-sale/neo-geo-rebuild/

ads.title: Atari Flashback 9 AR3050 HDMI
ads.description:
\ud83c\udfae Atari Flashback 9 (AR3050 HDMI) Overview
Released on November 15, 2018, the Atari Flashback 9 (AR3050) is a plug-and-play dedicated retro console built by AtGames under license from Atari 

Comes pre-loaded with 110 classic Atari games, outputting at 720p via HDMI.

Includes two wired joystick controllers, along with an SD card slot for playing additional games, saving states, and receiving firmware updates 

\u2728 Features & Performance Highlights
HDMI output ensures crisp visuals on modern HDTVs without needing old-style composite cables 

The SD card slot allows custom ROM playback and easy firmware updates\u2014something users praise as a standout improvement over earlier models 

The built-in emulation uses the Stella emulator (v3.x) for Atari 2600 titles and handles gameplay smoothly.

ads.title: NBA Maximum Hangtime, Upright Arcade, Midway GAmes 1996
ads.description:
Vintage Upright Arcade \u2013 NBA Maximum Hangtime (Midway Games, 1996)
Price: $600 or best offer
Take it back to the golden age of arcade basketball with this original NBA Maximum Hangtime upright cabinet from Midway, released in 1996. Known as the follow-up to NBA Jam and NBA Hangtime, this game delivers fast-paced, over-the-top basketball action with dunks, alley-oops, and classic 90s sports flair. It\u2019s a must-have for fans of Midway\u2019s legendary sports lineup.
Condition:
- Cabinet is very old and needs a lot of love.
- Lights come on.
- Monitor powers up and makes a hum, but no image \u2014 likely needs new caps.
- Boards and internals are present but untested.
- Sold as-is.
Highlights:
- Classic Midway basketball arcade with 2-on-2 gameplay.
- Upright cabinet design with iconic late-90s artwork.
- Great candidate for restoration or display in a retro collection.
Important:
- Price is $600, or best offer.
- Serious buyers only.

ads.author: Tom Grizzard
ads.title: 1992 Konami X-Men video arcade (PLEASE READ COMMENTS)
ads.description:
1992 Konami X-Men video arcade game is a retro collectible arcade gaming machine that allows players to experience the popular X-Men franchise through interactive gameplay. With Konami's reputation for quality and innovation, this arcade game offers a nostalgic gaming experience for fans of the series and collectors of vintage arcade machines. Featuring the iconic X-Men characters and storyline, this video arcade game is a must-have for any gaming enthusiast looking to add a piece of arcade history to their collection.

THE GOOD: Cabinet is in great overall condition. Monitor has no issues. Joysticks work fine, might be loose for some likeness/favor but nothing a new centering grommet would not solve... and not seized for removal as I did remove to clean and made adjustments, and shafts were cleaned well so wouldn't seize in near future (for easy removal).

THE BAD:  Original gameboard took a dump on me, and cost to replace is hovering around $1000.00... so, I installed a Pandora's DX box (turning off all games except X-men, so boots directly into game) and wiring the player 3 and player 4 control in via two "USB Joystick" pcb wiring adapters. The Pandora DX does support 4 players in Konomi X-Men with only one quirk that is not an issue... when you start either player three or player four you get player three, followed by player four... no big deal at all... besides that one super minor quirk everything works as it should.  To be clear, you can play a three player or a four player game no problem, and you can pick who is each... you just get player 3 controls first regardless if you hit player 3 or player 4 start, followed by play 4 controls if you hit either player 3 or player 4 start after starting a 3 player game first.  I see no sound or video issues WHATSOEVER playing X-Men on the Pandora's Box DX... NONE!  

As a convenience, I added 4 free-play buttons just above each of the coin chutes (small red start push buttons like on 1980's midway cocktail tables, barely noticeable) on the two top coindoors for any home user purchase.... those can easily be taken disabled and the coin mechs for all four players work fine if buyer wishes to collected revenue.

Will ship via freight carrier at Buyer's expense.  Local pickup allowed and encouraged (zip 31525). Local delivery (from Savannah down to Jacksonville) available for nominal fee.

ads.author: Brandon Ledford
ads.title: Street Fever Basketball Arcade Machine Rare
ads.description: The Street Fever Basketball Arcade Machine by Ice is an original game featuring the popular Street Fever theme. Players can enjoy a nostalgic gaming experience with this arcade-style basketball machine that is sure to bring back memories of classic games. With its original design and high-quality construction, this machine is a must-have for any arcade or gaming enthusiast looking to add a retro touch to their collection. Very Similar on Full Court Fever. Both games gives the player a moving hoop with a back and forth movement. Also the "Rotating" turntable that enables the player to shoot from every possible spot on the court. Game height is adjustable to either 8, 8.5 or 9 feet. Full Court Fever or Street Fever are also an accurate representation of basketball. We use a 7 inch ball and a 14 inch hoop so the proportions are correct. Has some minor scratches on the side, but works great.
